# Portal feature (CRUD)

**Canonical reference:** `portal/admin/features/vehicles/` — follow this layout for new admin list + create + edit features.

User features follow the same `data/` / `form/` layout — reference: `portal/user/features/transport/`. User list features split **All** vs **Our** into sibling folders `table-all/` and `table-our/` with a shared feature-root `*.table.ts` factory (`buildTransportTable`, `buildFreightTable`, `buildWarehouseTable`).

## Folder layout

```
features/<entity>/
  data/
    ...
  <entity>.table.ts          # user — build*Table('all' | 'our') factory + exported table constants
  form/
    ...
  table/                     # admin (single list)
    <entity>.table.ts
    <entity>-table-page.component.{ts,html,scss}
  table-all/                 # user — external company items
    <entity>-all-table-page.component.{ts,html,scss}
  table-our/                 # user — session company items
    <entity>-our-table-page.component.{ts,html,scss}
  detail/                    # user + admin detail pages
    ...
```

## data/

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `*.model.ts` | `EntityFormModel` interface; `Entity extends EntityFormModel` with `id`; union types for enums; **`status` on entity** (not form model unless editable) — see `entity-status.mdc` |
| `*.constants.ts` | `ADMIN_<ENTITY>_API` / `USER_<ENTITY>_API` (HTTP only — not app URLs); option arrays reused by form + table filters |
| `*.mock-data.ts` | `ENTITY_MOCK_DATA: Entity[]` |
| `*.service.ts` | `@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })`; in-memory `store` from mock; **`list()`** (admin) or **`listAll()` / `listOurs()`** (user) applies `TableQuery`; `getById`, `create`, `update`, `delete` with `delay()` until API; **`create()` default `status`**; **`update()` preserve `status`** — see `entity-status.mdc` |

Service naming: `AdminVehicleService`, `UserTransportService`, etc. Table page components inject as `transportService`, `freightService`, `warehouseService` (camelCase field name). Swap mock store for `HttpClient` later — keep the same method signatures.

## Routes + nav + URLs

1. **`shared/constants/admin-urls.ts`** or **`user-urls.ts`** — create URL, detail URL, edit URL builder, hub URLs; re-exported by `app-urls.ts` (see `app-urls.mdc`).
   - **User entities:** `USER_HOME_URL`, `USER_OUR_LISTINGS_URL`, `userMarketplaceUrl()` / `userOurListingsUrl()` (TS navigation), `userMarketplaceRoute()` / `userOurListingsRoute()` (`routerLink`), `USER_CREATE_<ENTITY>_URL`, `userEdit<Entity>Url(id)`, `user<Entity>DetailUrl(id)`. No standalone list URL constants.
2. **`admin.routes.ts`** (or `user.routes.ts`) — children under portal shell:
   - **Admin:** `home` hub (`/admin/home?tab=`); per entity `<entity>/create`, `<entity>/:id` (detail), `<entity>/:id/edit`; `settings`. List tables embedded in home hub. Row click → `admin*DetailUrl(id)`. Create via topbar `EntityCreateMenuComponent`. Form back/save → `adminHomeUrl(matchingTab)`.
   - **User:** `home` (marketplace hub), `our-listings` hub routes; per entity only `<entity>/create`, `<entity>/:id`, `<entity>/:id/edit`. Create via topbar `EntityCreateMenuComponent`. List tables embedded in hub pages. Form save redirects to `userOurListingsUrl(matchingEntity)`.
3. **`user-topbar-nav.config.ts`** — `topbarNav: []`; brand → marketplace; create via `EntityCreateMenuComponent`; my listings via account menu — see `layout.mdc`.
4. **User services:** `listAll()` / `listOurs()` with company scoping (`companyId` on entity; session `companyId`); `create()` sets ownership from session.

### Admin hub page

| Feature folder | Route | Role |
|----------------|-------|------|
| `features/home/` | `/admin/home?tab=` | `.page-hub-header` → `PageTitleComponent` + `EntityTabsComponent` (default `accentMode="entity"`) + embedded table pages; create via topbar only |

Tab config: `portal/admin/admin-entity-tabs.config.ts` → `ADMIN_ENTITY_TAB_CONFIG`. Tab sync: `syncHubEntityTab()` + `parseAdminEntityTab`.

### User hub pages

| Feature folder | Route | Role |
|----------------|-------|------|
| `features/home/` | `/home?tab=` | `.page-hub-header` → `PageHeaderComponent` + tab publish CTA + `EntityTabsComponent` + embedded `*AllTablePageComponent` |
| `features/our-listings/` | `/our-listings?tab=` | Same hub chrome + embedded `*OurTablePageComponent` |

Tab config: `portal/user/user-entity-tabs.config.ts` → `USER_ENTITY_TAB_CONFIG`. Tab sync: `syncHubEntityTab()` + `parseUserEntityTab`.

Angular `path` segments in `*.routes.ts` stay relative (`vehicles`, `create`, `:id/edit`); only absolute URLs go in the domain URL files (`admin-urls.ts` for admin CRUD).

## Form page (`form/<entity>-form-page.component.ts`)

- `FormBuilder` group mirrors every field key; validators on the group, not only in the def.
- `entityId` signal from `route.snapshot.paramMap`; `isEdit = computed(() => entityId() !== null)`.
- `stepperDataReady = signal(false)` — `true` on create init; after edit `patchValue` in `queueMicrotask`.
- `formDef` computed — swap submit action for create vs edit (`*FormEditActions` pattern).
- `ngOnInit`: no `:id` → `stepperDataReady.set(true)`; with `:id` → `getById` → `patchValue` (strip `id`) → `stepperDataReady.set(true)`; load error → `navigateByUrl` list URL.
- `onSubmit`: guard `submitting`; `getRawValue() as FormModel`; create vs update; success → list URL. Do not re-validate — `FormPageComponent` already did.
- `backUrl` + `backLabelKey` — list URL and nav label for `PageBackLinkComponent` (admin: `adminHomeUrl(matchingTab)` + `ADMIN_HOME_BACK_LABEL_KEY`; user: `userOurListingsUrl(matchingEntity)` + `OUR_LISTINGS_BACK_LABEL_KEY` / `portal.user.nav.ourListings`).
- Template:

```html
<app-page-back-link [route]="backUrl" [labelKey]="backLabelKey" [form]="form" />
<app-page-title [titleKey]="pageTitleKey()" [subtitleKey]="pageSubtitleKey()" [icon]="pageIcon" />
<app-form-page
  [definition]="formDef()"
  [formGroup]="form"
  [submitDisabled]="submitting()"
  [stepperMode]="isEdit() ? 'edit' : 'create'"
  [stepperDataReady]="stepperDataReady()"
  (submit)="onSubmit()"
/>
```

- `pageTitleKey` / `pageSubtitleKey` computed — swap create vs edit `portal.<portal>.pages.*` keys; `pageIcon` from `AdminPageIcons` / `UserPageIcons` (same on list + create + edit).

- Stepper UX (free navigation, `ValidationState` pills, submit-only enforcement, mobile layout): see `forms.mdc` — do not implement in the feature page.

### User transport / freight / warehouse (single-step + shared table display)

Reference: `portal/user/features/transport/`, `portal/user/features/freight/`, `portal/user/features/warehouse/`.

- **Form def:** `mode: 'single'`; origin/destination `type: 'autocomplete'` with `BIH_CITY_OPTIONS`; date periods via `type: 'datePeriod'` (`endKey` for ranges, `periodMode: 'single'` for needed-by) — see `forms.mdc`, `shared-constants.mdc`
- **Form page:** date validators from `shared/utils/date-input.ts`; re-validate end date when start changes; `pageIcon` from `UserPageIcons`; inject service as `transportService` / `freightService` / `warehouseService`
- **Dynamic select options:** `buildTransportForm(vehicleOptions)` / `buildWarehouseForm(warehouseOptions)` — clone form def, inject loaded options
- **Denormalized display on create/update:**
  - Transport: `CompanyVehicleService.getDisplay(vehicleId)` → `vehicleName`, `vehiclePlate`
  - Warehouse: `CompanyWarehouseService.getDisplay(warehouseId)` → `warehouseName`, `warehouseCity`; `getLabel()` → `warehouseLabel`
- **Table display widgets** (see `tables.mdc` for templates):
  - Transport + freight: `app-route-display` (route col), `app-status-badge`, `app-date-range-display` (merged period or single needed-by)
  - Transport only: `app-vehicle-display`
  - Warehouse: `app-warehouse-display` (name + city), `app-status-badge`, `app-date-range-display` (availability period)
- **Portal data:** `portal/user/data/company-vehicle.service.ts`, `company-warehouse.service.ts` for cross-feature selects

## Table page (`table/<entity>-table-page.component.ts`)

- `protected readonly table = EntityTable` (or `TransportAllTable` / `TransportOurTable` from feature-root factory).
- **User hub tables:** render `<app-data-table>` only — hub pages own title, tabs, and create CTA. See `entity-tabs.mdc`.
- **Admin hub tables:** same — embedded in `features/home/`; `[rowClickEnabled]="true"` → `admin*DetailUrl(id)`; detail page Edit/Delete in footer.
- **Standalone admin table (legacy pattern):** `app-page-header` with projected `app-page-title` + `app-primary-action-link` above `<app-data-table>`. Not used when tables live in home hub only.

```html
<app-page-header>
  <app-page-title [titleKey]="pageTitleKey" [subtitleKey]="pageSubtitleKey" [icon]="pageIcon" />
  <app-primary-action-link [route]="createUrl" [labelKey]="createLabelKey" />
</app-page-header>

@if (tableMounted()) {
  <app-data-table [definition]="table" [loader]="loadEntities" (rowAction)="onRowAction($event)" />
}
```

```typescript
import { PageHeaderComponent } from '…/shared/ui/page-header/page-header.component';
import { PageTitleComponent } from '…/shared/ui/page-title/page-title.component';
import { PrimaryActionLinkComponent } from '…/shared/ui/primary-action-link/primary-action-link.component';
import { AdminPageIcons } from '…/portal/admin/admin-page-icons';
import { ADMIN_CREATE_ENTITY_URL } from '…/shared/constants/app-urls';

protected readonly pageTitleKey = 'portal.admin.pages.<entity>.title';
protected readonly pageSubtitleKey = 'portal.admin.pages.<entity>.subtitle';
protected readonly pageIcon = AdminPageIcons.<entity>;
protected readonly createUrl = ADMIN_CREATE_ENTITY_URL;
protected readonly createLabelKey = 'portal.admin.nav.createEntity';

imports: [PageHeaderComponent, PageTitleComponent, PrimaryActionLinkComponent, DataTableComponent, …],
```

- Custom enum/display cells: `tableCellKey(Table, 'column')` + `<ng-template [appTableCell]="key" let-row>` + `| translate` on label keys.
- **Status cell:** `app-status-badge` + `status` column — see `entity-status.mdc`, `tables.mdc`.
- **Route / date / vehicle / warehouse cells:** shared display components — see `tables.mdc` (do not use raw text or duplicate badge markup).
- Row actions in `onRowAction`: `edit` → `navigateByUrl(editUrl(id))`; `delete` → `ConfirmService` then `service.delete` (see `confirm.mdc`).
- After delete: remount table via `tableMounted` signal (`false` → `queueMicrotask` → `true`).

```typescript
// Delete flow (abbreviated)
this.confirmService.confirm({ titleKey, messageKey, danger: true })
  .pipe(filter(Boolean), take(1), switchMap(() => this.service.delete(id)))
  .subscribe({ next: () => this.refreshTable() });
```

## Table def (`<entity>.table.ts`)

User entities — feature root with scope factory:

```typescript
export function buildTransportTable(scope: 'all' | 'our') {
  return defineTable<Transport>()({
    filterStorageKey: scope === 'our' ? TRANSPORT_OUR_FILTER_STORAGE_KEY : TRANSPORT_ALL_FILTER_STORAGE_KEY,
    // columns, filters, actions differ by scope …
  });
}
export const TransportAllTable = buildTransportTable('all');
export const TransportOurTable = buildTransportTable('our');
```

- `endpoint` from `*.constants.ts` (future HTTP).
- `trackBy: 'id'`; `defaultSort`; `mobile.primary` on the main identifier column.
- **List filters (user + admin):** colocate defs in `data/*-table-filters.ts`; reuse shared partials from `shared/table/user-list-filter-partials.ts` (`routeCityFilters`, `entityStatusFilter`) where applicable; set `filters` + `filterStorageKey` on table def; mock services apply via `applyTableFilters()` — see `table-filters.mdc`. Our-scope keys use `.our` suffix (e.g. `bhcom-ba.filters.user.freight.our`).
- `actions.items`: scope-specific (marketplace: view + send request; our: view + edit + delete); handle IDs in the page, not in the def.
- Reuse form option `labelKey`s in filter `options` where enums overlap.

## Detail pages

- User: `buildDetailPageActions('user', entity, { isOwnListing, editRoute })` from `shared/detail/detail-page.constants.ts`; navigation via `entity-detail-navigation.ts` (`EntityDetailOrigin = 'marketplace' | 'our'`).
- Admin: `buildDetailPageActions('admin', entity, { editRoute })`; back/subtitle via `portal/admin/common/admin-entity-detail-navigation.ts`.

## i18n

Namespace: `portal.<admin|user>.features.<entity>.{form|table}.*`

- Route titles: `portal.<portal>.pages.*`
- Nav: `portal.<portal>.nav.*`
- Delete dialog: `…table.deleteConfirm.title` / `…message`; buttons use `shared.confirm.common.*`

Add keys to **both** `public/assets/en.json` and `bh.json` (see `i18n.mdc`).

## Do not

- Cross-import `portal/admin/features/**` ↔ `portal/user/features/**`.
- Hardcode app paths — use `app-urls.ts`.
- Use `window.confirm` or per-page dialog markup — use `ConfirmService`.
- Add `*.spec.ts` files.
- Rebuild table/form chrome outside `DataTableComponent` / `FormPageComponent`.
- Omit `PageBackLinkComponent` on portal create/edit form pages — see `page-title.mdc`.
- Put create CTAs inside `DataTableComponent` or `PageTitleComponent` — use `PageHeaderComponent` + `PrimaryActionLinkComponent` on the page instead.
- Render page titles inside `DataTableComponent` or `FormPageComponent` — page templates use `PageTitleComponent` (`page-title.mdc`).
- Register standalone user list routes or `/offer` picker page — create flows use topbar `EntityCreateMenuComponent`.

